# Pollinations.ai API

Base URL: `https://gen.pollinations.ai`

## Endpoints

### Image Generation
```
GET /image/{prompt}?model=flux&width=1024&height=1024&seed=42&nologo=true
POST /image/generate (OpenAI Images API compatible)
```
Models: `flux`, `gptimage`, `gptimage-large`, `seedream5`, `nanobanana`, `nanobanana-pro`, `kontext`

### Text Generation (OpenAI-compatible)
```
POST /v1/chat/completions
  {"model": "openai", "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]}
GET /text/{prompt}?model=openai
```
Models: `openai`, `openai-large`, `claude`, `claude-large`, `gemini`, `gemini-large`, `deepseek`, `grok`, `mistral`, `qwen-coder`

### Audio / TTS
```
GET /audio/{text}?voice=nova
POST /v1/audio/speech (OpenAI TTS compatible)
```

### Video
```
POST /v1/chat/completions with model: "seedance" | "veo"
```

## Authentication
- No API key needed for basic usage (rate-limited per IP)
- `pk_` keys: client-safe, higher rate limits
- `sk_` keys: server-side, can spend Pollen credits
- Header: `Authorization: Bearer YOUR_KEY` or query: `?key=YOUR_KEY`

## SDKs
```bash
npm install @pollinations_ai/sdk        # JS/TS SDK
npm install @pollinations/react          # React hooks
pip install pollinations                 # Python
```

## Anti-patterns
- Do NOT use `image.pollinations.ai` or `text.pollinations.ai` directly — use `gen.pollinations.ai`
- Do NOT hardcode model names — fetch from `/v1/models` or `/image/models`
- Do NOT store API keys in client-side code — use `pk_` keys for frontend, `sk_` for backend
